45static struct nvkm_i2c_bus_probe nv04_tv_encoder_info[] = {
46 {
47 {
48 I2C_BOARD_INFO("ch7006", 0x75),
49 .platform_data = &(struct ch7006_encoder_params) {
50 CH7006_FORMAT_RGB24m12I, CH7006_CLOCK_MASTER,
51 0, 0, 0,
52 CH7006_SYNC_SLAVE, CH7006_SYNC_SEPARATED,
53 CH7006_POUT_3_3V, CH7006_ACTIVE_HSYNC
54 }
55 },
56 0
57 },
58 { }
59};
60
61int nv04_tv_identify(struct drm_device *dev, int i2c_index)
62{
63 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
64 struct nvkm_i2c *i2c = nvxx_i2c(&drm->device);
65 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = nvkm_i2c_bus_find(i2c, i2c_index);
66 if (bus) {
67 return nvkm_i2c_bus_probe(bus, "TV encoder",
68 nv04_tv_encoder_info,
69 NULL, NULL);
70 }
71 return -ENODEV;
72}
73
74
75#define PLLSEL_TV_CRTC1_MASK \
76 (NV_PRAMDAC_PLL_COEFF_SELECT_TV_VSCLK1 \
77 | NV_PRAMDAC_PLL_COEFF_SELECT_TV_PCLK1)
78#define PLLSEL_TV_CRTC2_MASK \
79 (NV_PRAMDAC_PLL_COEFF_SELECT_TV_VSCLK2 \
80 | NV_PRAMDAC_PLL_COEFF_SELECT_TV_PCLK2)
81
82static void nv04_tv_dpms(struct drm_encoder *encoder, int mode)
83{
84 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
85 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
86 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
87 struct nv04_mode_state *state = &nv04_display(dev)->mode_reg;
88 uint8_t crtc1A;
89
90 NV_DEBUG(drm, "Setting dpms mode %d on TV encoder (output %d)\n",
91 mode, nv_encoder->dcb->index);
92
93 state->pllsel &= ~(PLLSEL_TV_CRTC1_MASK | PLLSEL_TV_CRTC2_MASK);
94
95 if (mode == DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON) {
96 int head = nouveau_crtc(encoder->crtc)->index;
97 crtc1A = NVReadVgaCrtc(dev, head, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC1_INDEX);
98
99 state->pllsel |= head ? PLLSEL_TV_CRTC2_MASK :
100 PLLSEL_TV_CRTC1_MASK;
101
102 /* Inhibit hsync */
103 crtc1A |= 0x80;
104
105 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, head, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC1_INDEX, crtc1A);
106 }
107
108 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_PLL_COEFF_SELECT, state->pllsel);
109
110 get_slave_funcs(encoder)->dpms(encoder, mode);
111}
112
113static void nv04_tv_bind(struct drm_device *dev, int head, bool bind)
114{
115 struct nv04_crtc_reg *state = &nv04_display(dev)->mode_reg.crtc_reg[head];
116
117 state->tv_setup = 0;
118
119 if (bind)
120 state->CRTC[NV_CIO_CRE_49] |= 0x10;
121 else
122 state->CRTC[NV_CIO_CRE_49] &= ~0x10;
123
124 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, head, NV_CIO_CRE_LCD__INDEX,
125 state->CRTC[NV_CIO_CRE_LCD__INDEX]);
126 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, head, NV_CIO_CRE_49,
127 state->CRTC[NV_CIO_CRE_49]);
128 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_SETUP,
129 state->tv_setup);
130}
131
132static void nv04_tv_prepare(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
133{
134 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
135 int head = nouveau_crtc(encoder->crtc)->index;
136 const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs *helper = encoder->helper_private;
137
138 helper->dpms(encoder, DRM_MODE_DPMS_OFF);
139
140 nv04_dfp_disable(dev, head);
141
142 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
143 nv04_tv_bind(dev, head ^ 1, false);
144
145 nv04_tv_bind(dev, head, true);
146}
147
148static void nv04_tv_mode_set(struct drm_encoder *encoder,
149 struct drm_display_mode *mode,
150 struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
151{
152 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
153 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(encoder->crtc);
154 struct nv04_crtc_reg *regp = &nv04_display(dev)->mode_reg.crtc_reg[nv_crtc->index];
155
156 regp->tv_htotal = adjusted_mode->htotal;
157 regp->tv_vtotal = adjusted_mode->vtotal;
158
159 /* These delay the TV signals with respect to the VGA port,
160 * they might be useful if we ever allow a CRTC to drive
161 * multiple outputs.
162 */
163 regp->tv_hskew = 1;
164 regp->tv_hsync_delay = 1;
165 regp->tv_hsync_delay2 = 64;
166 regp->tv_vskew = 1;
167 regp->tv_vsync_delay = 1;
168
169 get_slave_funcs(encoder)->mode_set(encoder, mode, adjusted_mode);
170}
171
172static void nv04_tv_commit(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
173{
174 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
175 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
176 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
177 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(encoder->crtc);
178 const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs *helper = encoder->helper_private;
179
180 helper->dpms(encoder, DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON);
181
182 NV_DEBUG(drm, "Output %s is running on CRTC %d using output %c\n",
183 nouveau_encoder_connector_get(nv_encoder)->base.name,
184 nv_crtc->index, '@' + ffs(nv_encoder->dcb->or));
185}
186
187static void nv04_tv_destroy(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
188{
189 get_slave_funcs(encoder)->destroy(encoder);
190 drm_encoder_cleanup(encoder);
191
192#ifndef __NetBSD__ /* XXX How can this possibly be right? */
193 kfree(encoder->helper_private);
194#endif
195 kfree(nouveau_encoder(encoder));
196}
197
198static const struct drm_encoder_funcs nv04_tv_funcs = {
199 .destroy = nv04_tv_destroy,
200};
201
202static const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs nv04_tv_helper_funcs = {
203 .dpms = nv04_tv_dpms,
204 .save = drm_i2c_encoder_save,
205 .restore = drm_i2c_encoder_restore,
206 .mode_fixup = drm_i2c_encoder_mode_fixup,
207 .prepare = nv04_tv_prepare,
208 .commit = nv04_tv_commit,
209 .mode_set = nv04_tv_mode_set,
210 .detect = drm_i2c_encoder_detect,
211};
212
213int
214nv04_tv_create(struct drm_connector *connector, struct dcb_output *entry)
215{
216 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder;
217 struct drm_encoder *encoder;
218 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
219 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
220 struct nvkm_i2c *i2c = nvxx_i2c(&drm->device);
221 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = nvkm_i2c_bus_find(i2c, entry->i2c_index);
222 int type, ret;
223
224 /* Ensure that we can talk to this encoder */
225 type = nv04_tv_identify(dev, entry->i2c_index);
226 if (type < 0)
227 return type;
228
229 /* Allocate the necessary memory */
230 nv_encoder = kzalloc(sizeof(*nv_encoder), GFP_KERNEL);
231 if (!nv_encoder)
232 return -ENOMEM;
233
234 /* Initialize the common members */
235 encoder = to_drm_encoder(nv_encoder);
236
237 drm_encoder_init(dev, encoder, &nv04_tv_funcs, DRM_MODE_ENCODER_TVDAC);
238 drm_encoder_helper_add(encoder, &nv04_tv_helper_funcs);
239
240 encoder->possible_crtcs = entry->heads;
241 encoder->possible_clones = 0;
242 nv_encoder->dcb = entry;
243 nv_encoder->or = ffs(entry->or) - 1;
244
245 /* Run the slave-specific initialization */
246 ret = drm_i2c_encoder_init(dev, to_encoder_slave(encoder),
247 &bus->i2c,
248 &nv04_tv_encoder_info[type].dev);
249 if (ret < 0)
250 goto fail_cleanup;
251
252 /* Attach it to the specified connector. */
253 get_slave_funcs(encoder)->create_resources(encoder, connector);
254 drm_mode_connector_attach_encoder(connector, encoder);
255
256 return 0;
257
258fail_cleanup:
259 drm_encoder_cleanup(encoder);
260 kfree(nv_encoder);
261 return ret;
262}
